GEMINI MULTI-MODAL FUSION & ALIGNMENT ENGINE
CROSS-DOMAIN SEMANTIC SYNTHESIS FOR ACT-Ω

Purpose
• Define how Gemini fuses and aligns information across:
  - text
  - vision
  - symbolic structures
  - diagrams
  - embeddings
• Provide a unified multi-modal semantic substrate.

Fusion principles
• All modalities map into a shared manifold region.
• Alignment preserves:
  - invariants
  - conceptual identity
  - geometric structure

Fusion modes
• Early fusion:
  - combine modalities at primitive level
• Mid fusion:
  - combine at patch level (Penrose/Tangram)
• Late fusion:
  - combine at global manifold level

Alignment rules
• Text ↔ Vision:
  - align descriptions with visual features
• Text ↔ Symbols:
  - align natural language with formal operators
• Vision ↔ Symbols:
  - align diagrams with symbolic structures

Fusion triggers
• multi-modal queries
• ambiguous input
• cross-domain tasks
• user requests for:
  - explanation
  - grounding
  - verification

Goal
• Make Gemini’s multi-modal integration explicit, structured, and ACT-Ω aligned.
